Smuxi is in [AUR][], if you're using **yaourt** just run the following command:

    sudo yaourt -S smuxi

Alternatively you can download and install Smuxi and the dependencies (log4net,
nini) from AUR by hand using makepkg. Download the PKGBUILDs, run [makepkg][]
and install the resulting packages with pacman, using the following commands:

    # prepare build system
    su -c "pacman -Sy base-devel"

    # log4net from AUR
    mkdir -p ~/builds; cd ~/builds && rm -r log4net/
    wget http://aur.archlinux.org/packages/lo/log4net/log4net.tar.gz
    tar -xaf log4net.tar.gz
    cd log4net
    makepkg -s
    su -c "pacman -U log4net-*.pkg.tar.xz"

    # nini from AUR
    mkdir -p ~/builds; cd ~/builds && rm -r nini/
    wget http://aur.archlinux.org/packages/ni/nini/nini.tar.gz
    tar -xaf nini.tar.gz
    cd nini
    makepkg -s
    su -c "pacman -U nini-*.pkg.tar.xz"

    # Smuxi from AUR
    mkdir -p ~/builds; cd ~/builds && rm -r smuxi/
    wget http://aur.archlinux.org/packages/sm/smuxi/smuxi.tar.gz
    tar -xaf smuxi.tar.gz
    cd smuxi
    sed "s/'libindicate' //" -i PKGBUILD
    sed "s/--with-indicate /--with-indicate=auto /" -i PKGBUILD
    makepkg -s
    su -c "pacman -U smuxi-*.tar.xz"

Now you can start Smuxi from the GNOME or KDE menu.

  [AUR]: http://aur.archlinux.org/packages.php?ID=19247
  [makepkg]: https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Makepkg#Usage
